section.section:
Of the 12 Commission members:
1 shall be an individual from the Renal Administrators Association;
3 shall be individuals who are laypersons to the field of medicine;
3 shall be individuals appointed at the discretion of the Governor who:
Are medical specialists or other patient care providers in nephrology or kidney transplants; and
Do not have any direct ownership in renal dialysis or kidney transplant centers that do business in the State;
4 shall be individuals appointed as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection; and
1 shall be a renal social worker nominated by the Maryland Chapter of the Council of Nephrology Social Workers or the National Capital Area Chapter of the Council of Nephrology Social Workers.

Except as provided in subparagraph (iv) of this paragraph, the Governor shall appoint 1 member from a list of individuals submitted to the Governor by each of the following organizations:
The Kidney Foundation of Maryland;
The faculty of the University of Maryland School of Medicine;
The faculty of the Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine; and
The Medical and Chirurgical Faculty of the State of Maryland.
